  "text_preview": "\"world\" American Sign Language (ASL) ASL Lessons | Bookstore | Library | ASL University Main ► WORLD: The American Sign Language (ASL) sign for \"world\" To do the sign for \"world\" (if you are right handed) hold your right \"W\" hand on top of your left \"W\" hand. Move both hands simultaneously. The movement is a circular motion: forward, down, back, up. While the right hand is moving forward, the left hand is moving backward. When the right hand is moving upward, the left hand is moving downward. WORLD: There are many variations for how to sign \"WORLD\" depending on the context you are using. THE WHOLE WORLD / WORLD: GLOBAL / ALL OVER THE WORLD: INTERNATIONAL / GLOBE / WORLD: There are 3 variations for \"AROUND THE WORLD.\" AROUND THE WORLD (version 1): AROUND THE WORLD (version 2): AROUND THE WO"
}
